1
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:15,233
You'll make many friends
if you go to a regular school.

2
00:00:15,300 --> 00:00:16,500
Kids who are our age.

3
00:00:16,567 --> 00:00:18,733
The school doesn't discriminate
against people like you.

4
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:20,200
Why are you talking
to my daughter?

5
00:00:20,267 --> 00:00:24,067
I was just telling your daughter
that she'd enjoy regular school.

6
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:26,200
Leave before I call the police.

7
00:00:26,267 --> 00:00:26,933
Leave!

8
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:29,333
Maybe I can enroll here.

9
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:30,367
You stay here.

10
00:00:31,833 --> 00:00:34,900
You enjoy caring for a baby
who's not related to you.

11
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:38,800
Mom, anyone doesn't have to be
our relative

12
00:00:38,867 --> 00:00:40,533
for us to love them, right?

13
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:41,800
What's that for?

14
00:00:41,867 --> 00:00:43,733
This is for your immune system.

15
00:00:45,967 --> 00:00:46,567
What happened?

16
00:00:46,633 --> 00:00:50,500
Why can't I move my legs?

17
00:00:50,567 --> 00:00:52,000
Mommy!

18
00:00:52,067 --> 00:00:53,733
- Mookie! What happened?
- Mommy!

19
00:00:53,800 --> 00:00:55,533
Why are you on the floor?

20
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:57,500
You're going to be fine.

21
00:01:31,633 --> 00:01:33,400
Mom!

22
00:01:33,467 --> 00:01:34,633
We bought it.

23
00:01:34,700 --> 00:01:36,533
- The vitamins?
- Yes.

24
00:01:37,833 --> 00:01:43,367
The doctor said this would help
her become active and strong.

25
00:01:43,467 --> 00:01:46,267
And that's what we gave
Baby Kayla before.

26
00:01:46,333 --> 00:01:47,300
Yes.

27
00:01:47,367 --> 00:01:48,733
That's effective.

28
00:01:51,633 --> 00:01:54,267
Mom, where's Baby Samantha?

29
00:01:54,333 --> 00:01:56,700
I left her sleeping earlier.

30
00:01:56,767 --> 00:01:58,933
That's why I was able
to play cards, wait.

31
00:02:00,833 --> 00:02:02,633
Oh, wow.

32
00:02:02,700 --> 00:02:05,167
That baby is awake.

33
00:02:05,233 --> 00:02:07,033
How are you?

34
00:02:09,967 --> 00:02:11,633
You're hot.

35
00:02:11,700 --> 00:02:12,700
Come here.

36
00:02:12,767 --> 00:02:15,133
Oh, no. Let go of that.

37
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:17,800
- Emma.
- Mom.

38
00:02:17,867 --> 00:02:19,833
Can you check her?
She seems hot.

39
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:20,767
What?

40
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:26,000
Yeah. She has a high fever.

41
00:02:26,067 --> 00:02:27,700
- She's hot.
- I'll get her a cover.

42
00:02:27,767 --> 00:02:29,800
- Let's bring her to the center?
- Come on, let's go.

43
00:02:29,867 --> 00:02:31,433
- Let's go to the health center.
- Here, here.

44
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:34,767
- Bring that.
- Please cover her, Mom.

45
00:02:34,833 --> 00:02:37,567
Wait, baby.

46
00:02:37,633 --> 00:02:41,433
No, no, no, it's nothing.

47
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:43,967
- Hurry up.
- We'll get going, Mom.

48
00:02:55,733 --> 00:02:57,433
Do you feel anything, Mookie?

49
00:03:06,133 --> 00:03:08,167
Mommy, what's happening?

50
00:03:08,233 --> 00:03:09,867
Let me try this.

51
00:03:27,700 --> 00:03:28,700
Mommy.

52
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,567
Your reflexes are hyperactive.

53
00:03:37,633 --> 00:03:42,267
And this indicates that you
may have an injury or damage

54
00:03:42,333 --> 00:03:44,700
in your spinal cord.

55
00:03:44,767 --> 00:03:47,500
That's why you've lost
your legs' muscle function.

56
00:03:49,567 --> 00:03:52,800
Mommy, what do we do?

57
00:03:52,867 --> 00:03:56,433
Like procedures?
What do we need to do?

58
00:04:01,467 --> 00:04:03,933
I think we need to put you
in a wheelchair.

59
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:10,833
Doc!

60
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:13,900
Doc! Please help us.
My daughter has a fever.

61
00:04:18,267 --> 00:04:20,033
Yes, her temperature is high.

62
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:21,800
How long has she had a fever?

63
00:04:21,867 --> 00:04:23,933
She doesn't feel hot
this morning.

64
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:27,100
Then she suddenly
became feverish.

65
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:28,767
What do you think happened
to the child, Doc?

66
00:04:28,833 --> 00:04:30,167
We still have to examine her.

67
00:04:30,233 --> 00:04:33,067
So we'll know what medicine
we can give the child.

68
00:04:33,133 --> 00:04:35,400
We can't just give her
any medicine.

69
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:43,000
I don't want to, Mommy!

70
00:04:44,333 --> 00:04:47,000
Why did I get paralyzed, Mommy?

71
00:04:50,067 --> 00:04:52,633
You know what, Dear,
I don't know, either.

72
00:04:52,700 --> 00:04:55,933
But it looks like your condition
is acting out again.

73
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:57,267
You're getting worse.

74
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:01,233
This is what I'm scared of.

75
00:05:03,700 --> 00:05:05,700
Clearly, you aren't healed yet.

76
00:05:06,833 --> 00:05:11,133
Good thing it happened
when I was here.

77
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:13,267
What if this happened outside?

78
00:05:13,333 --> 00:05:15,133
Who will take care of you?

79
00:05:17,667 --> 00:05:19,100
Dear...

80
00:05:19,167 --> 00:05:22,833
you're so lucky to have me.

81
00:05:27,633 --> 00:05:28,600
Mommy...

82
00:05:30,067 --> 00:05:32,200
can I still walk?

83
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:34,533
Mookie, sweetie,

84
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:36,667
I don't know.

85
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,000
I don't know.

86
00:05:41,367 --> 00:05:43,733
But if I were you,

87
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:46,600
don't get your hopes up.

88
00:05:46,667 --> 00:05:53,533
Because there's a big chance
that you can never walk again.

89
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:54,233
What?

90
00:05:58,367 --> 00:06:00,633
Get some rest today, okay?

91
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:07,900
- Mommy.
- Come on.

92
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,600
- Flor, help me.
- Yes, Ma'am.

93
00:06:09,667 --> 00:06:12,767
- Let's put her to bed.
- Mommy.

94
00:06:12,833 --> 00:06:18,167
Mommy, what's happening?

95
00:06:18,233 --> 00:06:19,767
Mommy.

96
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:27,267
It's okay, Mookie.

97
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:28,967
It's okay.

98
00:06:29,033 --> 00:06:32,267
Mommy, what about my enrollment?

99
00:06:33,967 --> 00:06:34,933
Enrollment?

100
00:06:36,100 --> 00:06:37,900
Mookier, dear.

101
00:06:37,967 --> 00:06:39,733
Look at you.

102
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:41,167
You can't walk.

103
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:46,833
Clearly, you're not ready
to go to school on your own.

104
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:52,867
So, you'll stay at home.

105
00:06:52,933 --> 00:06:53,967
Okay?

106
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:35,033
Dan, what if I gave Samantha
something that caused her fever?

107
00:07:35,100 --> 00:07:38,900
That's the recommended dosage,
right?

108
00:07:38,967 --> 00:07:40,867
Why does she have a fever now?
Look at her.

109
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:45,000
Maybe it's just
because she's growing.

110
00:07:45,067 --> 00:07:47,433
I can't bear to see
children suffer.

111
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:48,733
I can't bear it.

112
00:07:51,667 --> 00:07:52,500
Doc.

113
00:07:52,567 --> 00:07:54,800
Doc, how's Samantha, my child?

114
00:07:54,867 --> 00:07:56,833
Her fever has gone down.

115
00:07:59,100 --> 00:08:00,100
Is she feeling better now, Doc?

116
00:08:00,167 --> 00:08:02,833
Yes, monitor her for 24 hours.

117
00:08:02,900 --> 00:08:05,333
And if her fever comes back,
bring her here immediately.

118
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:08,033
Thank you, Doc. Thank you.

119
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:09,467
Dear.

120
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:14,000
- We're going home.
- Hold on.

121
00:08:14,067 --> 00:08:18,400
We're going home.

122
00:08:18,467 --> 00:08:20,133
Emma...

123
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:22,967
why did you call her your child?

124
00:08:23,067 --> 00:08:24,600
- Did I?
- Yes.

125
00:08:24,667 --> 00:08:26,000
I didn't notice.

126
00:08:26,067 --> 00:08:27,767
Emma, I hope you don't
take it the wrong way.

127
00:08:27,833 --> 00:08:32,667
But I'm reminding you,
she's not our daughter.

128
00:08:32,733 --> 00:08:35,267
You're getting too attached
to the kid.

129
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:38,867
When her mother returns,
you have to give her back.

130
00:08:38,933 --> 00:08:40,867
Dan, I know that.

131
00:08:40,933 --> 00:08:43,367
Maybe I just panicked,
because...

132
00:08:44,867 --> 00:08:46,133
That's why I said that.

133
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:49,067
Maybe I remembered Kayla
when we had to confine her.

134
00:08:55,100 --> 00:08:59,000
Flor, what's happening?
Why can't I move my legs?

135
00:08:59,067 --> 00:09:01,900
Mookie, sorry.
I really don't know.

136
00:09:01,967 --> 00:09:03,333
Mookie, please stop.

137
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:06,600
Flor, I thought I could
finally go to school.

138
00:09:06,667 --> 00:09:08,900
I thought I'd be
a normal teenager.

139
00:09:08,967 --> 00:09:12,567
But why did this happen?
I was just given a false hope!

140
00:09:12,633 --> 00:09:14,467
That's enough. Stop.

141
00:09:14,533 --> 00:09:17,667
Who knows?
Maybe you can walk again.

142
00:09:17,733 --> 00:09:19,867
That's enough.

143
00:09:19,933 --> 00:09:22,933
- Walk again?
- Yes.

144
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:27,533
Mommy said...

145
00:09:29,467 --> 00:09:31,967
this could be permanent.

146
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:37,000
Olive, don't you really think

147
00:09:37,067 --> 00:09:39,200
we have to bring Mookie
to the hospital?

148
00:09:39,267 --> 00:09:40,667
I mean, this is really serious.

149
00:09:42,233 --> 00:09:43,633
I'm already taking care of it.

150
00:09:45,033 --> 00:09:46,633
It's just weird.

151
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:48,167
Of all days,

152
00:09:48,233 --> 00:09:50,100
the day she was going to enroll
in school,

153
00:09:50,167 --> 00:09:52,267
her legs got paralyzed.

154
00:09:52,333 --> 00:09:53,867
I wonder what's the trigger.

155
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:59,167
Well, clearly,
her condition is getting worse.

156
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:01,300
Poor Mookie.

157
00:10:03,133 --> 00:10:06,700
I thought I was improving.

158
00:10:06,767 --> 00:10:08,633
I thought I was getting better.

159
00:10:10,467 --> 00:10:12,533
Why is it like this, Flor?

160
00:10:15,767 --> 00:10:18,367
Why does my illness
seem to get worse?

161
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:28,033
Why do I feel like
I'm not getting better?

162
00:10:29,833 --> 00:10:31,600
Why is it like this, Flor?

163
00:10:32,733 --> 00:10:35,900
I want to get better.
I want to recover.

164
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,500
Yes.

165
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:45,000
I'm actually relieved
that happened to her.

166
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:47,433
Why so?

167
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:51,933
I really didn't want her
to go to school.

168
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:55,033
I want her to stay home so...

169
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:56,700
I can always look after her.

170
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:02,633
You sound like you wanted this
to happen to your daughter.

171
00:11:07,433 --> 00:11:09,367
Anyway,

172
00:11:09,467 --> 00:11:11,800
I'm done here.
I think I have to go.

173
00:11:21,133 --> 00:11:22,400
Canixidol?

174
00:11:24,967 --> 00:11:26,200
Give me that.

175
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:30,300
That's for animals.

176
00:11:30,367 --> 00:11:32,567
It causes muscle paralysis.

177
00:11:32,633 --> 00:11:33,767
Why do you have that?

178
00:11:38,833 --> 00:11:40,100
Olive.

179
00:11:40,167 --> 00:11:41,633
Did you give that Mookie,

180
00:11:41,733 --> 00:11:43,633
that's why she suddenly
can't walk?

181
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,900
Olive.

182
00:11:55,967 --> 00:11:57,633
Did you give that Mookie,

183
00:11:57,700 --> 00:11:59,767
that's why she suddenly
can't walk?

184
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:03,067
Of course not!

185
00:12:03,133 --> 00:12:05,200
Why would I administer this
to her?

186
00:12:05,267 --> 00:12:06,633
Why is it empty?

187
00:12:06,700 --> 00:12:07,833
Where did you use that?

188
00:12:10,833 --> 00:12:12,567
Astrid,

189
00:12:12,633 --> 00:12:14,367
are you implying something?

190
00:12:17,533 --> 00:12:18,500
No.

191
00:12:18,567 --> 00:12:19,533
No.

192
00:12:21,333 --> 00:12:24,100
A mother is accused
of medical child abuse,

193
00:12:24,167 --> 00:12:26,567
also known
as Munchausen syndrome

194
00:12:26,633 --> 00:12:31,033
by proxy against her 10-year-old
daughter, Abigail Smith.

195
00:12:31,100 --> 00:12:34,733
Even though Abigail was healthy,
the mother overdosed her child

196
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:38,800
and had her undergo multiple
surgeries, leading to her death.

197
00:12:38,867 --> 00:12:40,967
Hey, Emma.

198
00:12:41,033 --> 00:12:43,267
Watch this.

199
00:12:43,333 --> 00:12:44,967
There's a case in America.

200
00:12:45,033 --> 00:12:47,300
The kid is seriously ill.

201
00:12:47,367 --> 00:12:50,833
Turns out the mother
only made it up.

202
00:12:50,933 --> 00:12:53,367
She's injecting various
medicines into the kid

203
00:12:53,433 --> 00:12:54,933
to make her sick.

204
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:58,500
Why would she do that, Mom?

205
00:12:58,567 --> 00:13:01,900
So that the child
won't leave her.

206
00:13:01,967 --> 00:13:03,200
So that the kid stays with her.

207
00:13:03,267 --> 00:13:07,200
She wants her child to depend on
her even if she's already old.

208
00:13:07,267 --> 00:13:08,333
Oh, no.

209
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:11,700
That woman is probably
mentally ill.

210
00:13:11,767 --> 00:13:14,400
It says that she has a...

211
00:13:14,467 --> 00:13:17,300
How do I pronounce this?

212
00:13:17,367 --> 00:13:21,633
Munchausen by proxy.

213
00:13:21,733 --> 00:13:22,900
Whatever.

214
00:13:22,967 --> 00:13:23,900
That's it.

215
00:13:23,967 --> 00:13:26,833
What kind of a mother
do you think I am?

216
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:29,433
That I would intentionally
hurt my daughter?

217
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:32,967
Olive, I'm sorry.

218
00:13:33,033 --> 00:13:34,167
But don't you really think

219
00:13:34,233 --> 00:13:36,300
we have to bring Mookie
to the hospital?

220
00:13:38,267 --> 00:13:40,100
Why?

221
00:13:40,167 --> 00:13:42,833
I mean,
this is life-threatening.

222
00:13:42,900 --> 00:13:45,267
We can't ignore this.

223
00:13:45,333 --> 00:13:47,433
I am not bringing her
to any hospital

224
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:50,233
because I don't trust
other doctors.

225
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:53,600
And I am the only doctor
she needs.

226
00:13:55,533 --> 00:13:57,467
I'm just concerned with the kid.

227
00:14:00,967 --> 00:14:02,100
You know what, Astrid?

228
00:14:04,100 --> 00:14:05,433
This will be the last time

229
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:08,567
you will ever talk to me
about my daughter.

230
00:14:08,633 --> 00:14:12,033
Because she's none
of your business.

231
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:13,233
I just want to help.

232
00:14:13,300 --> 00:14:14,667
I know you do.

233
00:14:16,333 --> 00:14:18,667
But you're just
making things worse.

234
00:14:38,633 --> 00:14:41,467
- Anybody home?
- Come in.

235
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:43,967
Emma?

236
00:14:44,033 --> 00:14:45,733
Melissa, come in.

237
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:48,633
Hello, Miss Ligaya.
Good afternoon.

238
00:14:50,533 --> 00:14:53,167
I thought you'd come back
next month?

239
00:14:53,233 --> 00:14:55,100
I returned earlier
than expected.

240
00:14:55,167 --> 00:14:57,100
My child's papers
have been approved.

241
00:14:57,167 --> 00:15:00,067
Hi, Baby. That's why I'm going
to get her back.

242
00:15:00,133 --> 00:15:01,767
Come.

243
00:15:01,867 --> 00:15:03,733
It's me, Mom.

244
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:04,800
Why?

245
00:15:07,967 --> 00:15:10,400
Samantha, it's me, your mom.

246
00:15:10,467 --> 00:15:11,800
Why?

247
00:15:14,500 --> 00:15:17,000
Are you picking her up today?

248
00:15:17,067 --> 00:15:22,300
Yes. Because I need
to go somewhere else.

249
00:15:22,367 --> 00:15:23,767
You know what?

250
00:15:23,833 --> 00:15:26,367
The kid cried the moment
she heard your voice.

251
00:15:26,433 --> 00:15:28,767
She wasn't crying earlier.

252
00:15:28,833 --> 00:15:31,167
Can I hold her again?

253
00:15:31,233 --> 00:15:32,400
Sure.

254
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:38,567
Is it okay if you pick her up
next week?

255
00:15:38,633 --> 00:15:40,167
She just recovered
from sickness.

256
00:15:40,233 --> 00:15:43,067
She might get sick again
if she travels.

257
00:15:43,133 --> 00:15:46,233
I'm leaving for Macau
on Saturday.

258
00:15:46,300 --> 00:15:50,667
She'll be leaving with me,
that's why I need to get her.

259
00:15:50,733 --> 00:15:53,500
So that's why she's crying.
She's sick.

260
00:15:53,567 --> 00:15:55,133
That's why she's crying.

261
00:16:05,100 --> 00:16:07,700
Go on, Emma.
Give Melissa her child.

262
00:16:11,133 --> 00:16:12,100
Come on.

263
00:16:16,333 --> 00:16:18,533
Emma, give her to Melissa.

264
00:16:24,833 --> 00:16:26,400
Wait, wait. We'll go home now.

265
00:16:26,467 --> 00:16:27,733
Wait, okay?

266
00:16:27,800 --> 00:16:30,467
Danilo, can you get
Samantha's things?

267
00:16:36,933 --> 00:16:39,367
This belongs to Samantha.

268
00:16:39,433 --> 00:16:40,967
It's her stuff.

269
00:16:41,033 --> 00:16:41,667
Wait.

270
00:16:41,767 --> 00:16:43,267
Before we forget.

271
00:16:43,333 --> 00:16:45,000
- Where's your payment?
- Oh, yeah.

272
00:16:45,067 --> 00:16:45,800
Wait.
You don't have to.

273
00:16:46,700 --> 00:16:47,767
Mom, she doesn't have to.

274
00:16:47,833 --> 00:16:49,133
Melissa, you don't have to pay.

275
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:51,133
Are you sure? It's in my pocket.

276
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:53,067
No. Samantha needs it more.

277
00:16:53,133 --> 00:16:56,067
- Look.
- Okay, I'll get going.

278
00:16:56,133 --> 00:16:57,133
Okay.

279
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:58,400
Thank you.

280
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:57,733
Astrid?

281
00:17:57,800 --> 00:17:58,667
Doc Charles!

282
00:17:58,733 --> 00:18:00,100
Please, just call me Charles.

283
00:18:00,167 --> 00:18:02,733
You talk as if
we weren't classmates before.

284
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:04,033
Okay, okay. Charles.

285
00:18:04,100 --> 00:18:05,600
What are you doing here?

286
00:18:05,667 --> 00:18:08,633
I just finished
my speaking engagement.

287
00:18:08,700 --> 00:18:09,900
Oh, okay.

288
00:18:09,967 --> 00:18:12,567
Are you still working at
St. Agnes Children's Hospital?

289
00:18:12,633 --> 00:18:14,900
Yes, I still do clinic there.

290
00:18:14,967 --> 00:18:17,800
- Nice to hear. Nice to see you.
- Nice to see you.

291
00:18:17,867 --> 00:18:19,667
Bye.

292
00:18:19,733 --> 00:18:22,700
Oh, by the way.

293
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:27,733
How's your friend Olive?

294
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:29,600
She's doing okay,
we were together last time.

295
00:18:29,667 --> 00:18:31,467
Why did you ask?

296
00:18:31,533 --> 00:18:35,667
I was just wondering
about her daughter.

297
00:18:35,733 --> 00:18:37,867
Mookie?

298
00:18:37,933 --> 00:18:40,000
I was her pediatrician before.

299
00:18:42,067 --> 00:18:43,400
I didn't know that.

300
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:45,433
You know what?

301
00:18:45,500 --> 00:18:50,733
That was a very strange case.

302
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:53,800
Why?

303
00:18:53,867 --> 00:18:58,800
Olive was insisting that
the child had many illnesses.

304
00:18:58,900 --> 00:19:02,000
But when we ran some tests,

305
00:19:02,067 --> 00:19:04,467
we didn't see anything.

306
00:19:04,533 --> 00:19:07,733
In fact, she was
perfectly healthy.

307
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:11,767
And when we showed
Olive the results,

308
00:19:11,833 --> 00:19:13,833
she was so angry.

309
00:19:13,900 --> 00:19:15,633
She pulled out the kid.

310
00:19:15,700 --> 00:19:17,100
Mookie.

311
00:19:17,167 --> 00:19:20,567
Charles, when did that happen?

312
00:19:20,633 --> 00:19:22,767
Almost 10 years ago?

313
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:27,033
Anyway, I shouldn't be
telling you this

314
00:19:27,100 --> 00:19:31,500
because of breaching
doctor-patient confidentiality.

315
00:19:33,767 --> 00:19:38,333
I'm just curious
what happened to the child.

316
00:20:10,033 --> 00:20:12,267
I'm already 17.

317
00:20:12,333 --> 00:20:15,700
I'll be an adult soon.

318
00:20:15,767 --> 00:20:22,300
I want to know how it feels
to be in the outside world.

319
00:20:22,367 --> 00:20:25,100
How it feels
to be a normal teenager.

320
00:21:02,667 --> 00:21:05,200
Mommy!

321
00:21:05,267 --> 00:21:07,900
Mommy!

322
00:21:11,833 --> 00:21:13,333
Canixidol?

323
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:15,033
That's for animals.

324
00:21:15,100 --> 00:21:17,267
It causes muscle paralysis.

325
00:21:17,333 --> 00:21:18,533
Why do you have that?

326
00:21:21,367 --> 00:21:24,033
Olive, did you give it
to Mookie?

327
00:21:24,100 --> 00:21:26,233
That's why she can't walk?

328
00:21:27,833 --> 00:21:28,833
Mommy,

329
00:21:30,367 --> 00:21:32,833
can I still walk?

330
00:21:33,767 --> 00:21:35,000
I don't know.

331
00:21:35,867 --> 00:21:38,400
But if I were you,

332
00:21:38,467 --> 00:21:41,267
don't get your hopes up.

333
00:21:41,333 --> 00:21:46,300
Because there's a big chance
that you can never walk again.

334
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:13,733
Mommy?

335
00:22:17,433 --> 00:22:18,933
Yes?

336
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:22,267
Mookie, what is it?

337
00:22:22,333 --> 00:22:25,600
I just want to say good night.

338
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:29,467
- Okay.
- Good night.

339
00:22:35,467 --> 00:22:36,967
Don't touch anything.

340
00:22:37,033 --> 00:22:38,867
I got it. I'll take care of it.

341
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:42,100
I said don't touch it!

342
00:22:45,467 --> 00:22:46,433
Go!

343
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:48,833
Okay.

344
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:12,767
Do we really have to move out?

345
00:23:12,833 --> 00:23:15,633
It's better for Emma
if we leave.

346
00:23:15,700 --> 00:23:18,633
Because it has
so many sad memories.

347
00:23:18,700 --> 00:23:20,633
I didn't want to do this.

348
00:23:20,700 --> 00:23:24,133
I don't want to interfere
with your private life.

349
00:23:24,233 --> 00:23:29,333
But this medical report
proves that Mookie isn't sick.

350
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:31,567
That she's actually
a healthy kid.

351
00:23:31,633 --> 00:23:33,533
These documents
don't mean anything.

352
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:35,533
These were 10 years ago.

353
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:38,133
You said Mookie has been ill
since she was young.

354
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:40,367
That medical report
was 10 years ago.

355
00:23:40,433 --> 00:23:42,333
That means you
were lying before.

356
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:44,833
Is Mookie really sick? Or...

357
00:23:44,900 --> 00:23:46,467
are you just making it all up?
